flavorText: This Pokémon shares many similarities with Iron Hands, an object mentioned in a certain expedition journal.

name: Iron Thorns

attacks.name: Destructo-Press
attacks.text: Reveal the top 5 cards of your deck. This attack does 70 damage for each Future card you find there. Then, discard those Future cards and shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

flavorText: Some of its notable features match those of an object named within a certain expedition journal as Iron Thorns.

name: Azumarill

attacks.name: Play Rough
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Power Tackle
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

flavorText: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.

name: Girafarig

attacks.name: Psychic Assault
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Girafarig's tail has a small head. It instinctively bites at any foe that approaches the Pokémon from behind.

name: Latias

attacks.name: Allure
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

flavorText: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.

name: Bronzor

attacks.name: Mirror Attack
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Psychic Pokémon, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor's back contained a mysterious power.

name: Bronzong

attacks.name: Evolution Jammer
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Pokémon from their hand to evolve their Pokémon.

flavorText: In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.

name: Solosis

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It communicates with others telepathically. Its body is encapsulated in liquid, but if it takes a heavy blow, the liquid will leak out.

name: Duosion

attacks.name: Double Trick
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

flavorText: Its psychic power can supposedly cover a range of more than half a mile—but only if its two brains can agree with each other.

name: Reuniclus

attacks.name: Summoning Gate
attacks.text: Look at the top 8 cards of your deck. You may put any number of Pokémon you find there onto your Bench. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

attacks.name: Brain Shake
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: While it could use its psychic abilities in battle, this Pokémon prefers to swing its powerful arms around to beat opponents into submission.

name: Elgyem

attacks.name: Hide
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: If this Pokémon stands near a TV, strange scenery will appear on the screen. That scenery is said to be from its home.

name: Beheeyem

attacks.name: Cosmic Beatdown
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Pokémon in play.

flavorText: Whenever a Beheeyem visits a farm, a Dubwool mysteriously disappears.

name: Cutiefly

attacks.name: Mini Drain
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare. You can find Cutiefly hovering around Gossifleur, trying to get some of Gossifleur's pollen.

name: Ribombee

attacks.name: Plentiful Pollen
attacks.text: During your next turn, if the Defending Pokémon is Knocked Out, take 2 more Prize cards.

flavorText: It makes pollen puffs from pollen and nectar. The puffs' effects depend on the type of ingredients and how much of each one is used.

name: Flutter Mane

abilities.name: Midnight Fluttering
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent's Active Pokémon has no Abilities, except for Midnight Fluttering.

attacks.name: Hex Hurl
attacks.text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Benched Pokémon in any way you like.

flavorText: This Pokémon has characteristics similar to those of Flutter Mane, a creature mentioned in a certain book.

name: Iron Valiant

attacks.name: Gemini Laser
attacks.text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Zen Blade
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Zen Blade.

flavorText: It's possible that this is the object listed as Iron Valiant in a certain expedition journal.

name: Iron Crown ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Cobalt Command
abilities.text: Attacks used by your Future Pokémon, except any Iron Crown ex, do 20 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Twin Shotels
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on those Pokémon.

name: Meditite
flavorText: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.

name: Medicham
flavorText: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the same motion.

name: Relicanth

abilities.name: Memory Dive
abilities.text: Each of your evolved Pokémon can use any attack from its previous Evolutions. (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)

flavorText: Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokémon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.

name: Excadrill

attacks.name: Wild Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

flavorText: It's not uncommon for tunnels that appear to have formed naturally to actually be a result of Excadrill's rampant digging.

name: Golett

attacks.name: Iron Defense
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks.

flavorText: They were sculpted from clay in ancient times. No one knows why, but some of them are driven to continually line up boulders.

name: Golurk

attacks.name: Iron Defense
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks.

attacks.name: Fighting Fist
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex or Pokémon V, this attack does 120 more damage.

flavorText: Artillery platforms built into the walls of ancient castles served as perches from which Golurk could fire energy beams.

name: Lycanroc

attacks.name: Turbo Edge
attacks.text: Attach up to 2 Basic Fighting Energy cards from your discard pile to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like.

flavorText: Lycanroc attacks its prey with its sharp claws and fangs. It loyally obeys the instructions of a Trainer it trusts.

name: Mudbray
flavorText: This Pokémon covers itself in mud that it has regurgitated. The mud won't dry out even if it's exposed to the sun for a long time.

name: Mudsdale

attacks.name: Mud Stock
attacks.text: Attach a Basic Fighting Energy card from your discard pile to each of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: High Horsepower
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 40 damage to itself.

flavorText: This Pokémon has been treasured not just for its physical labor but also because it produces high-quality mud used for making pottery.

name: Rolycoly
flavorText: On sunny days, Rolycoly will come out onto grassy plains and roll around. Then it will eat the grass that gets tangled in its wheel-like leg.

name: Carkol

attacks.name: Knock Away
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

flavorText: The temperature inside its body increases when it experiences strong emotions. It rolls around frantically while spewing flames.

name: Coalossal

attacks.name: Gatling Tar
attacks.text: This attack does 80 more damage for each Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Cragalanche
attacks.text: Discard the top 2 cards of your opponent's deck.

flavorText: To intimidate its opponents, Coalossal will vigorously shake its body, scattering coal from its smoldering back.

name: Great Tusk

attacks.name: Wrathful Charge
attacks.text: If your Benched Pokémon have any damage counters on them, this attack does 80 more damage.

flavorText: Sightings of this Pokémon have occurred in recent years. The name Great Tusk was taken from a creature listed in a certain book.

name: Sandy Shocks

attacks.name: Magnetic Burst
attacks.text: If you have 3 or more Energy in play, this attack does 70 more damage. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness.

flavorText: No records exist of this Pokémon being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon's traits match up with a creature shown in an expedition journal.

name: Iron Boulder ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Repulsor Axe
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if it is Knocked Out), put 8 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

attacks.name: Power Stomp
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Ekans

attacks.name: Poison Blend
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

flavorText: The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.

name: Arbok

attacks.name: Panic Poison
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned, Confused, and Poisoned.

flavorText: The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.

name: Gastly

attacks.name: Mysterious Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body, slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.

name: Haunter

attacks.name: Super Poison Breath
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.

name: Gengar ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Gnawing Curse
abilities.text: Whenever your opponent attaches an Energy card from their hand to 1 of their Pokémon, put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Tricky Steps
attacks.text: You may move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon to 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

name: Poochyena

attacks.name: Gnaw Off
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.

name: Mightyena

attacks.name: Kick Away
attacks.text: Switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

flavorText: It will always obey the commands of a skilled Trainer. Its behavior arises from its living in packs in ancient times.

name: Farigiraf ex
rules: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

abilities.name: Armor Tail
abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Basic Pokémon ex.

attacks.name: Dirty Beam
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Roaring Moon

attacks.name: Vengeance Fletching
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Ancient card in your discard pile.

flavorText: It is possible that this is the creature listed as Roaring Moon in an expedition journal that still holds many mysteries.

name: Forretress

attacks.name: Spike Cannon
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Steel Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 40 damage to itself.

flavorText: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside this shell is a total mystery.

name: Scizor ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Steel Wing
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 50 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Cross Breaker
attacks.text: Discard up to 2 Metal Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 120 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Beldum

attacks.name: Iron Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: From its rear, Beldum emits a magnetic force that rapidly pulls opponents in. They get skewered on Beldum's sharp claws.

name: Metang

abilities.name: Metal Maker
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 4 cards of your deck and attach any number of Basic Metal Energy cards you find there to your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards and put them on the bottom of your deck.

flavorText: Two Beldum have become stuck together via their own magnetic forces. With two brains, the resulting Metang has doubled psychic powers.

name: Metagross

attacks.name: Meteor Mash
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Meteor Mash attack does 60 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Luster Blast
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Because the magnetic powers of these Pokémon get stronger in freezing temperatures, Metagross living on snowy mountains are full of energy.

name: Meltan
flavorText: It dissolves and eats metal. Circulating liquid metal within its body is how it generates energy.

name: Melmetal
flavorText: At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.

name: Iron Treads

abilities.name: Dual Core
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon has a Future Booster Energy Capsule attached, it is Fighting and Metal type.

attacks.name: Wheel Pass
attacks.text: Move an Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Sightings of this Pokémon have occurred in recent years. It resembles a mysterious object described in an old expedition journal.

name: Koraidon

attacks.name: Primordial Beatdown
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Ancient Pokémon in play.

attacks.name: Shred
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.

name: Miraidon

attacks.name: Peak Acceleration
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards and attach them to your Future Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: This seems to be the Iron Serpent mentioned in an old book. The Iron Serpent is said to have turned the land to ash with its lightning.

name: Raging Bolt ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Burst Roar
attacks.text: Discard your hand and draw 6 cards.

attacks.name: Bellowing Thunder
attacks.text: You may discard any amount of Basic Energy from your Pokémon. This attack does 70 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Lickilicky

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Tonguenado
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.

flavorText: Lickilicky's strange tongue can stretch to many times the length of its body. No one has figured out how Lickilicky's tongue can stretch so far.

name: Hoothoot

attacks.name: Silent Wing
attacks.text: Your opponent reveals their hand.

flavorText: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.

name: Noctowl

attacks.name: Talon Hunt
attacks.text: You may search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.

name: Dunsparce

attacks.name: Dig
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It creates mazes in dark locations. When spotted, it flees into the ground by digging with its tail.

name: Skitty

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It can't stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in a circle, chasing its own tail.

name: Delcatty

attacks.name: Tail Trickery
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Energy Blender
attacks.text: You may move any amount of Energy from your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.

flavorText: It dislikes dirty places. It often searches for a comfortable place in which to groom itself.

name: Chatot

attacks.name: A Cappella
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them into thinking it's one of them. This way they won't attack it.

name: Pidove

abilities.name: Emergency Evolution
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon's remaining HP is 30 or less, you may search your deck for an Unfezant or Unfezant ex and put it onto this Pidove to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: Where people go, these Pokémon follow. If you're scattering food for them, be careful— several hundred of them can gather at once.

name: Tranquill

attacks.name: Jet Wing
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

flavorText: It can fly moderately quickly. No matter how far it travels, it can always find its way back to its master and its nest.

name: Unfezant

attacks.name: Opposing Winds
attacks.text: You may put 2 Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon into their hand.

attacks.name: Boundless Power
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

flavorText: Unfezant are exceptional fliers. The females are known for their stamina, while the males outclass them in terms of speed.

name: Minccino

attacks.name: Cleaning Up
attacks.text: Discard up to 2 Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.

name: Cinccino

attacks.name: Special Roll
attacks.text: This attack does 70 damage for each Special Energy card attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won't tolerate even a speck of the stuff.

name: Awakening Drum
rules: Draw a card for each of your Ancient Pokémon in play.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
ACE SPEC: You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

name: Bianca's Devotion
rules: Heal all damage from 1 of your Pokémon that has 30 HP or less remaining.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Boxed Order
rules: Search your deck for up to 2 Item cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. Your turn ends.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Buddy-Buddy Poffin
rules: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon with 70 HP or less and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Ciphermaniac's Codebreaking
rules: Search your deck for 2 cards, shuffle your deck, then put those cards on top of it in any order.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Eri
rules: Your opponent reveals their hand, and you discard up to 2 Item cards you find there.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Explorer's Guidance
rules: Look at the top 6 cards of your deck and put 2 of them into your hand. Discard the other cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Full Metal Lab
rules: Metal Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) take 30 less damage from attacks from the opponent's Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it into the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.

name: Hand Trimmer
rules: Each player discards cards from their hand until they have 5 cards in their hand. Your opponent discards first. (If a player has 5 or fewer cards in their hand, they do not discard.)
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Heavy Baton
rules: If the Pokémon this card is attached to has a Retreat Cost of exactly 4, is in the Active Spot, and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, move up to 3 Basic Energy cards from that Pokémon to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like.
You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.

name: Hero's Cape
rules: The Pokémon this card is attached to gets +100 HP.
You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.
ACE SPEC: You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

name: Master Ball
rules: Search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
ACE SPEC: You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

name: Maximum Belt
rules: Attacks used by the Pokémon this card is attached to do 50 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon ex (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.
ACE SPEC: You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

name: Morty's Conviction
rules: You can use this card only if you discard another card from your hand.  Draw a card for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Perilous Jungle
rules: During Pokémon Checkup, put 2 more damage counters on each Poisoned non-Darkness Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it next to the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it into the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.

name: Prime Catcher
rules: Switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot. If you do, switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
ACE SPEC: You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

name: Reboot Pod
rules: Attach a Basic Energy card from your discard pile to each of your Future Pokémon.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
ACE SPEC: You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

name: Rescue Board
rules: The Retreat Cost of the Pokémon this card is attached to is Colorless less. If that Pokémon's remaining HP is 30 or less, it has no Retreat Cost.
You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.

name: Salvatore
rules: Search your deck for a card that has no Abilities and evolves from 1 of your Pokémon, and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck. You can use this card on a Pokémon you put down when you were setting up to play or on a Pokémon that was put into play this turn.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Mist Energy
rules: As long as this card is attached to a Pokémon, it provides Colorless Energy.    Prevent all effects of attacks used by your opponent's Pokémon done to the Pokémon this card is attached to. (Existing effects are not removed. Damage is not an effect.)

name: Neo Upper Energy
rules: You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

As long as this card is attached to a Pokémon, it provides Colorless Energy.  If this card is attached to a Stage 2 Pokémon, this card provides every type of Energy but provides only 2 Energy at a time.
ACE SPEC: You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

name: Tangrowth

abilities.name: Thicket Body
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Loom Over
attacks.text: This attack does 10 less damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

flavorText: Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it pleases. Recent research has shown that these arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.

name: Pinsir

attacks.name: Slow Crunch
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon. At the end of your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon will be Knocked Out.

flavorText: These Pokémon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.

name: Spinarak
flavorText: Some fishers weave its sturdy thread into nets to catch fish Pokémon.

name: Ariados

abilities.name: Big Net
abilities.text: Your opponent's Active Evolution Pokémon's Retreat Cost is Colorless more.

attacks.name: String Bind
attacks.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

flavorText: It wanders in search of food after darkness falls, never nesting in a specific place.

name: Sunkern

attacks.name: Bullet Seed
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

flavorText: It is very weak. Its only means of defense is to shake its leaves desperately at its attacker.

name: Sunflora

attacks.name: Redirected Sunlight
attacks.text: This attack does 60 damage for each Fire Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Since it converts sunlight into energy, it is always looking in the direction of the sun.

name: Volbeat

attacks.name: Quick Sign
attacks.text: If you go first, you can use this attack during your first turn. Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Coordinated Strike
attacks.text: If Illumise is on your Bench, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: It flashes the light on its rear to communicate with other Volbeat. It loves the sweet aroma given off by Illumise.

name: Illumise

attacks.name: Slowing Perfume
attacks.text: You can use this attack only if you go second, and only during your first turn. Shuffle 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and all attached cards into their deck.

flavorText: It guides Volbeat to draw signs in the night sky. There are scholars who research the meaning of these signs.

name: Leafeon

attacks.name: Leaflet Blessings
attacks.text: Attach a Basic Grass Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you do, heal all damage from that Pokémon.

flavorText: The younger they are, the more they smell like fresh grass. With age, their fragrance takes on the odor of fallen leaves.

name: Phantump

attacks.name: Leech Seed
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon came to be when the spirit of a deceased child possessed a tree stump. It now wanders the forest searching for friends.

name: Trevenant

attacks.name: Giga Drain
attacks.text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Trevenant is very kind to Pokémon living in the forest. It doesn't even care if these Pokémon take up residence in the greenery on its head.

name: Grookey
flavorText: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

name: Thwackey

abilities.name: Boom Boom Groove
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if your Active Pokémon has the Festival Lead Ability, you may search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.

name: Rillaboom

attacks.name: Drum Beating
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon cost Colorless more, and its Retreat Cost is Colorless more.

attacks.name: Wood Hammer
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

flavorText: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

name: Applin

attacks.name: Tumbling Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: Applin lives inside an apple. When an Applin is separated from its apple, its body loses moisture and the Pokémon grows weak.

name: Dipplin

abilities.name: Festival Lead
abilities.text: If Festival Grounds is in play, this Pokémon may use an attack it has twice. If the first attack Knocks Out your opponent's Active Pokémon, you may attack again after your opponent chooses a new Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Do the Wave
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: The head sticking out belongs to the fore-wyrm, while the tail belongs to the core-wyrm. The two share one apple and help each other out.

name: Iron Leaves

attacks.name: Recovery Net
attacks.text: Put up to 2 Pokémon from your discard pile into your hand.

attacks.name: Avenging Edge
attacks.text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: According to the few eyewitness accounts that exist, it used its shining blades to julienne large trees and boulders.

name: Poltchageist

abilities.name: Storehouse Hideaway
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokémon done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Poltchageist looks like a regional form of Sinistea, but it was recently discovered that the two Pokémon are entirely unrelated.

name: Poltchageist

attacks.name: Tea Server
attacks.text: Put a Basic Grass Energy card from your discard pile into your hand.

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: Poltchageist looks like a regional form of Sinistea, but it was recently discovered that the two Pokémon are entirely unrelated.

name: Sinistcha

attacks.name: Cursed Drop
attacks.text: Put 4 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

attacks.name: Spill the Tea
attacks.text: Discard up to 3 Grass Energy cards from your Pokémon. This attack does 70 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

flavorText: It prefers cool, dark places, such as the back of a shelf or the space beneath a home's floorboards. It wanders in search of prey after sunset.

name: Sinistcha ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Re-Brew
attacks.text: Put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon for each Basic Grass Energy card in your discard pile. Then, shuffle those Energy cards into your deck.

attacks.name: Matcha Splash
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from each of your Pokémon.

name: Teal Mask Ogerpon

attacks.name: Mountain Stroll
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Ogre Comeback
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: This mischief-loving Pokémon is full of curiosity. It battles by drawing out the type-based energy contained within its masks.

name: Teal Mask Ogerpon ex
rules: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

abilities.name: Teal Dance
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Basic Grass Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, draw a card.

attacks.name: Myriad Leaf Shower
attacks.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to both Active Pokémon.

name: Magcargo ex
rules: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

attacks.name: Hot Magma
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Ground Burn
attacks.text: Discard the top card of each player's deck. This attack does 140 more damage for each Energy card discarded in this way.

name: Chimchar

attacks.name: Firebreathing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can't extinguish the fire.

name: Monferno

attacks.name: Heat Blow
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.

name: Infernape

abilities.name: Pyro Dance
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Basic Fire Energy card, a Basic Fighting Energy card, or 1 of each from your hand to your Pokémon in any way you like.

attacks.name: Scorching Fire
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.

name: Chandelure

abilities.name: Alluring Light
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may have each player draw a card.

attacks.name: Mind Ruler
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each card in your opponent's hand.

flavorText: It absorbs spirits, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

name: Hearthflame Mask Ogerpon ex
rules: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

attacks.name: Wrathful Hearth
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dynamic Blaze
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is an Evolution Pokémon, this attack does 140 more damage, and discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Poliwhirl

attacks.name: Hypnosis
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Double Slap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

flavorText: Its skin is moist all over its body. The skin on its belly spiral also feels smooth.

name: Poliwrath

attacks.name: Hypnosis
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Jumping Uppercut
attacks.text: You may do 120 more damage. If you do, shuffle this Pokémon and all attached cards into your deck.

flavorText: It can use its well-developed arms and legs to run on the surface of the water for a split second.

name: Goldeen

abilities.name: Festival Lead
abilities.text: If Festival Grounds is in play, this Pokémon may use an attack it has twice. If the first attack Knocks Out your opponent's Active Pokémon, you may attack again after your opponent chooses a new Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Whirlpool
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the Water Dancer.

name: Seaking

attacks.name: Peck Off
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.

name: Jynx

attacks.name: Inviting Kiss
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck. If you put any Pokémon onto your Bench in this way, move an Energy from this Pokémon to the new Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: In certain parts of Galar, Jynx was once feared and worshiped as the Queen of Ice.

name: Corphish
flavorText: It can live in impure water, where it doesn't need to compete with other water Pokémon for food, so its numbers have steadily increased.

name: Crawdaunt

attacks.name: Snip Snip
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

attacks.name: Rampaging Hammer
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

flavorText: A rough customer that wildly flails its giant claws. It is said to be extremely hard to raise.

name: Glalie

attacks.name: Damage Beat
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Crazy Headbutt
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It prevents prey from escaping by instantaneously freezing moisture in the air.

name: Froslass

abilities.name: Freezing Shroud
abilities.text: During Pokémon Checkup, put 1 damage counter on each Pokémon that has an Ability (both yours and your opponent's), except any Froslass.

flavorText: It freezes prey by blowing its −58 degree Fahrenheit breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.

name: Glaceon

attacks.name: Permeating Chill
attacks.text: At the end of your opponent's next turn, put 9 damage counters on the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.

name: Phione

attacks.name: Beckon
attacks.text: Put a Supporter card from your discard pile into your hand.

attacks.name: Energy Press
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: When the water warms, they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.

name: Froakie

attacks.name: Flock
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Froakie and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

name: Cramorant

attacks.name: Spit Shot
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It's an incredibly poor learner because it uses the bare minimum amount of energy for its brain. It focuses on battling instead.

name: Finizen

attacks.name: Aqua Slash
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

flavorText: Its water ring is made from seawater mixed with a sticky fluid that Finizen secretes from its blowhole.

name: Palafin

abilities.name: Zero to Hero
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when this Pokémon moves from the Active Spot to the Bench, you may search your deck for a Palafin ex and switch it with this Pokémon. Any attached cards, damage counters, Special Conditions, turns in play, and any other effects remain on the new Pokémon. If you switched a Pokémon in this way, put this card into your deck. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: Its physical capabilities are no different than a Finizen's, but when its allies are in danger, it transforms and powers itself up.

name: Palafin ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Hero's Spirit
abilities.text: Put this Pokémon into play only with the effect of Palafin's Zero to Hero Ability.

attacks.name: Giga Impact
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Iron Bundle

attacks.name: Interjet
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you do, switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

flavorText: It resembles a mysterious object mentioned in an old book. There are only two reported sightings of this Pokémon.

name: Walking Wake

attacks.name: Aurora Gain
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Undulating Slice
attacks.text: Put up to 9 damage counters on this Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter you placed in this way.

flavorText: This ferocious creature is shrouded in mystery. It's named after an aquatic monster mentioned in an old expedition journal.

name: Wellspring Mask Ogerpon ex
rules: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

attacks.name: Sob
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Torrential Pump
attacks.text: You may shuffle 3 Energy attached to this Pokémon into your deck. If you do, this attack also does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Zapdos

attacks.name: Thunder Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Thunderbolt
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon has complete control over electricity. There are tales of Zapdos nesting in the dark depths of pitch-black thunderclouds.

name: Shinx

attacks.name: Curiosity
attacks.text: Your opponent reveals their hand.

flavorText: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. Its fur glows when it's in trouble.

name: Luxray ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Piercing Gaze
attacks.text: Your opponent reveals their hand. Discard a card you find there.

attacks.name: Volt Strike
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Emolga

attacks.name: Sky Wave
attacks.text: This attack also does 10 damage to each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: As Emolga flutters through the air, it crackles with electricity. This Pokémon is cute, but it can cause a lot of trouble.

name: Helioptile

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

flavorText: When spread, the frills on its head act like solar panels, generating the power behind this Pokémon's electric moves.

name: Heliolisk

attacks.name: Wild Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: A now-vanished desert culture treasured these Pokémon. Appropriately, when Heliolisk came to the Galar region, treasure came with them.

name: Iron Thorns ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Initialization
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, Pokémon with a Rule Box in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities, except for Future Pokémon. (Pokémon ex, Pokémon V, etc. have Rule Boxes.)

attacks.name: Volt Cyclone
attacks.text: Move an Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Clefable

attacks.name: Metronome
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

flavorText: It has an acute sense of hearing. It can easily hear a pin being dropped nearly 1,100 yards away.

name: Abra

abilities.name: Teleporter
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may shuffle it and all attached cards into your deck.

flavorText: This Pokémon uses its psychic powers while it sleeps. The contents of Abra's dreams affect the powers that the Pokémon wields.

name: Alakazam

attacks.name: Strange Hacking
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused. You may move any number of damage counters from your opponent's Pokémon to their other Pokémon in any way you like.

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.

name: Swirlix

abilities.name: Festival Lead
abilities.text: If Festival Grounds is in play, this Pokémon may use an attack it has twice. If the first attack Knocks Out your opponent's Active Pokémon, you may attack again after your opponent chooses a new Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Sneaky Placement
attacks.text: Put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: It eats its own weight in sugar every day. If it doesn't get enough sugar, it becomes incredibly grumpy.

name: Slurpuff

attacks.name: Slurp Slurp
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 90 damage for each heads. If both of them are tails,  your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: By taking in a person's scent, it can sniff out their mental and physical condition. It's hoped that this skill will have many medical applications.

name: Enamorus

attacks.name: Love Resonance
attacks.text: If any of your Pokémon in play are the same type as any of your opponent's Pokémon in play, this attack does 120 more damage.

flavorText: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokémon's love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.

name: Scream Tail ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Scream
attacks.text: You can use this attack only if you go second, and only during your first turn. Your opponent can't play any Supporter cards from their hand during their next turn.

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Munkidori

abilities.name: Adrena-Brain
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon has any Darkness Energy attached, you may move up to 3 damage counters from 1 of your Pokémon to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Mind Bend
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Munkidori keeps itself somewhere safe while it toys with its foes, using psychokinesis to induce intense dizziness.

name: Fezandipiti

abilities.name: Adrena-Pheromone
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has any Darkness Energy attached and is damaged by an attack, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.

attacks.name: Energy Feather
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Fezandipiti beats its glossy wings to scatter pheromones that captivate people and Pokémon.

name: Hisuian Growlithe

attacks.name: Blazing Destruction
attacks.text: Discard a Stadium in play.

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: They patrol their territory in pairs. I believe the igneous rock components in the fur of this species are the result of volcanic activity in its habitat.

name: Hisuian Arcanine

attacks.name: Proud Fangs
attacks.text: If your Benched Pokémon have any damage counters on them, this attack does 90 more damage.

attacks.name: Searing Flame
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.

name: Nosepass

attacks.name: Power Rush
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, during your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

flavorText: When endangered, it may protect itself by increasing its magnetism and drawing nearby iron objects to its body.

name: Probopass

attacks.name: Assault Laser
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

flavorText: Probopass radiates such a powerful magnetic field that nearby electrical appliances are rendered useless while it's around.

name: Timburr

attacks.name: Best Punch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle heavy lumber without difficulty.

name: Gurdurr

attacks.name: Superpower
attacks.text: You may do 30 more damage. If you do, this Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

flavorText: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

name: Conkeldurr

attacks.name: Tantrum
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Gutsy Swing
attacks.text: If this Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, ignore all Energy in this attack's cost.

flavorText: Rather than rely on their strength, they master moves that make good use of centrifugal force to swing around concrete.

name: Greninja ex
rules: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

attacks.name: Shinobi Blade
attacks.text: You may search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Mirage Barrage
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 120 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Okidogi

abilities.name: Adrena-Power
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has any Darkness Energy attached, it gets +100 HP, and the attacks it uses do 100 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Okidogi is a ruffian with a short temper. It can pulverize anything by swinging around the chain on its neck.

name: Cornerstone Mask Ogerpon ex
rules: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

abilities.name: Cornerstone Stance
abilities.text: Prevent all damage from attacks done to this Pokémon by your opponent's Pokémon that have an Ability.

attacks.name: Demolish
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Venipede

attacks.name: Spit Poison
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Venipede and Sizzlipede are similar species, but when the two meet, a huge fight ensues.

name: Whirlipede

attacks.name: Poison Ring
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

flavorText: This Pokémon spins itself rapidly and charges into its opponents. Its top speed is just over 60 mph.

name: Scolipede

attacks.name: Dastardly Jab
attacks.text: Put damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon until its remaining HP is 10.

flavorText: Scolipede latches on to its prey with the claws on its neck before slamming them into the ground and jabbing them with its claws' toxic spikes.

name: Aron

attacks.name: Double-Edge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It eats iron ore—and sometimes railroad tracks— to build up the steel armor that protects its body.

name: Lairon

attacks.name: Steel Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: Lairon live in mountains brimming with spring water and iron ore, so these Pokémon often came into conflict with humans in the past.

name: Aggron

attacks.name: Angry Slam
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your Pokémon that has any damage counters on it.

attacks.name: Guard Claw
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 50 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Aggron has a horn sharp enough to perforate thick iron sheets. It brings down its opponents by ramming into them horn first.

name: Heatran

abilities.name: Incandescent Body
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Steel Burst
attacks.text: Discard all Metal Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 50 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

flavorText: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: Dreepy
flavorText: It has a habit of biting at Clauncher even though it doesn't feed on them. This is said to be vestigial behavior from when Dreepy was alive.

name: Drakloak

abilities.name: Recon Directive
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 2 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Put the other card on the bottom of your deck.

flavorText: This Pokémon stores up energy in its lungs, then shoots it out. It takes care of Dreepy and battles alongside them until they're all grown up.

name: Dragapult ex
rules: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

attacks.name: Phantom Dive
attacks.text: Put 6 damage counters on your opponent's Benched Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Farfetch'd

abilities.name: Impromptu Carrier
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may search your deck for a Pokémon Tool card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Mach Cut
attacks.text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.

name: Chansey

attacks.name: Lucky Attachment
attacks.text: Attach a Basic Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Boundless Power
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

flavorText: It walks carefully to prevent its egg from breaking. However, it is extremely fast at running away.

name: Blissey ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Happy Switch
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may move a Basic Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Return
attacks.text: You may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

name: Eevee

attacks.name: Ascension
attacks.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element stones.

name: Snorlax

attacks.name: But First, Food
attacks.text: Attach an Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon. If you do, heal 60 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Its stomach's digestive juices can dissolve any kind of poison. Eating things off the ground doesn't bother it at all.

name: Ambipom

abilities.name: Wicked Tail
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may flip 2 coins. For each heads, choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals those cards and shuffles them into their deck.

flavorText: Split into two, the tails are so adept at handling and doing things that Ambipom rarely uses its hands.

name: Ducklett

attacks.name: Double Draw
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

flavorText: It strengthens its body by diving into the depths of ponds, swimming around while looking for bog moss to eat.

name: Swanna

attacks.name: Fighting Wings
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex or Pokémon V, this attack does 90 more damage.

flavorText: It's said that many artists have taken inspiration from the sight of a Swanna performing a beautiful dance in the light of dawn.

name: Bloodmoon Ursaluna ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Seasoned Skill
abilities.text: Blood Moon used by this Pokémon costs Colorless less for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

attacks.name: Blood Moon
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Accompanying Flute
rules: Reveal the top 5 cards of your opponent's deck. You may choose any number of Basic Pokémon you find there and put those Pokémon onto their Bench. Your opponent shuffles the other cards back into their deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Bug Catching Set
rules: Look at the top 7 cards of your deck. You may reveal up to 2 in any combination of Grass Pokémon and Basic Grass Energy cards you find there and put them into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Caretaker
rules: Draw 2 cards. If you drew any cards in this way and if Community Center is in play, shuffle this Caretaker into your deck instead of discarding it.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Carmine
rules: If you go first, you may use this card during your first turn.    Discard your hand and draw 5 cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Community Center
rules: Once during each player's turn, if they played a Supporter card from their hand this turn, they may heal 10 damage from each of their Pokémon.
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it next to the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it into the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.

name: Cook
rules: Heal 70 damage from your Active Pokémon.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Enhanced Hammer
rules: Discard a Special Energy from 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Festival Grounds
rules: Each Pokémon that has any Energy attached (both yours and your opponent's) recovers from all Special Conditions and can't be affected by any Special Conditions.
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it into the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.

name: Handheld Fan
rules: If the Pokémon this card is attached to is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), move an Energy from the Attacking Pokémon to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.
You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.
Attach a Pokémon Tool to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn't already have a Pokémon Tool attached.

name: Hassel
rules: You can use this card only if any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out during your opponent's last turn.    Look at the top 8 cards of your deck and put up to 3 of them into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Hyper Aroma
rules: You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.
Search your deck for up to 3 Stage 1 Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
ACE SPEC: You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

name: Jamming Tower
rules: Pokémon Tools attached to each Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) have no effect.
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it into the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.

name: Kieran
rules: Choose 1:    • Switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.  • During this turn, attacks used by your Pokémon do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon ex and Active Pokémon V (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Lana's Aid
rules: Put up to 3 in any combination of Pokémon that don't have a Rule Box and Basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand. (Pokémon ex, Pokémon V, etc. have Rule Boxes.)
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Love Ball
rules: Search your deck for a Pokémon with the same name as 1 of your opponent's Pokémon in play, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Lucian
rules: Each player shuffles their hand and puts it on the bottom of their deck. If either player put any cards on the bottom of their deck in this way, each player flips a coin. If heads, that player draws 6 cards. If tails, they draw 3 cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Lucky Helmet
rules: If the Pokémon this card is attached to is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), draw 2 cards.
You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.
Attach a Pokémon Tool to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn't already have a Pokémon Tool attached.

name: Ogre's Mask
rules: Choose a Pokémon ex in your discard pile that has "Ogerpon" in its name, and switch it with 1 of your Pokémon ex in play that has "Ogerpon" in its name. Any attached cards, damage counters, Special Conditions, turns in play, and any other effects remain on the new Pokémon.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Perrin
rules: Reveal up to 2 Pokémon in your hand and put them into your deck. If you do, search your deck for up to that many Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Raifort
rules: Look at the top 5 cards of your deck and discard any number of them. Put the other cards back in any order.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Scoop Up Cyclone
rules: You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.
Put 1 of your Pokémon and all attached cards into your hand.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
ACE SPEC: You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

name: Hitmontop

attacks.name: Spin and Draw
attacks.text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 6 cards.

flavorText: It spins on its horn while dealing out elegant kicks. Its horn grows continuously through its lifetime.

name: Groudon

attacks.name: Megaton Fall
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

flavorText: Said to have expanded the lands by evaporating water with raging heat. It battled titanically with Kyogre.

name: Stunfisk ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Big Bite
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Flopping Trap
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Mega Hawlucha ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
Mega Evolution ex Rule: When your Mega Evolution Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Tenacious Body
abilities.text: If this Pokémon would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, flip a coin. If heads, this Pokémon is not Knocked Out, and its remaining HP becomes 10.

attacks.name: Somersault Dive
attacks.text: If a Stadium is in play, this attack does 140 more damage. Then, discard that Stadium.

abilities.name: Double Type
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in play, it is Fighting and Psychic type.

attacks.name: Counter Jewel
attacks.text: If your opponent has 2 or fewer Prize cards remaining, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Okidogi

attacks.name: Settle the Score
attacks.text: This attack does 60 more damage for each Prize card your opponent took during their last turn.

flavorText: Okidogi is a ruffian with a short temper. It can pulverize anything by swinging around the chain on its neck.

name: Team Rocket's Honchkrow

attacks.name: Rocket Feathers
attacks.text: You may discard any number of Supporter cards that have "Team Rocket" in their name from your hand, and this attack does 60 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

flavorText: A single cry from this nocturnal Pokémon, and more than 100 of its Murkrow cronies will assemble.

name: Galarian Zigzagoon
flavorText: Its restlessness has it constantly running around. If it sees another Pokémon, it will purposely run into them in order to start a fight.

name: Galarian Linoone
flavorText: It uses its long tongue to taunt opponents. Once the opposition is enraged, this Pokémon hurls itself at the opponent, tackling them forcefully.

name: Galarian Obstagoon

attacks.name: Scarring Shout
attacks.text: This attack does 70 damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Punk Smash
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shout—this move is known as Obstruct.

name: Scraggy

attacks.name: Knock Off
attacks.text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

flavorText: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

name: Mega Scrafty ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
Mega Evolution ex Rule: When your Mega Evolution Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Counterattacking Crest
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), place 5 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

attacks.name: Outlaw Leg
attacks.text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand. Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Mandibuzz ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Bone Shot
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Vulture Claw
attacks.text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Hoopa

attacks.name: Filch
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Knuckle Impact
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use attacks.

flavorText: This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.

name: Pecharunt

abilities.name: Final Chain
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Mochi Rush
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Mochi Rush attack does 50 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Its peach-shaped shell serves as storage for a potent poison. It makes poisonous mochi and serves them to people and Pokémon.

name: Registeel ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Regi Charge
attacks.text: Attach up to 2 Basic Metal Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Protecting Steel
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 50 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Togedemaru ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Stun Needle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Spiky Rolling
attacks.text: If this Pokémon used Spiky Rolling during your last turn, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Dratini
flavorText: This Pokémon is full of life energy. It continually sheds its skin and grows steadily larger.

name: Mega Dragonite ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
Mega Evolution ex Rule: When your Mega Evolution Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Sky Transport
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may use this Ability. Switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Ryuno Glide
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Rayquaza

attacks.name: Breakthrough Assault
attacks.text: If this Pokémon moved from your Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

flavorText: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.

name: N's Zekrom

attacks.name: Shred
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Rampaging Thunder
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use attacks.

flavorText: When the interior part of its tail spins like a motor, Zekrom can generate many bolts of lightning to blast its surroundings.

name: Noivern

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Enhanced Blade
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 70 more damage.

flavorText: They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. Nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.

name: Team Rocket's Kangaskhan ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Comet Punch
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Wicked Impact
attacks.text: If you played a Supporter card that has "Team Rocket" in its name from your hand during this turn, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Larry's Dunsparce

attacks.name: Rising Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: If spotted, it escapes by burrowing with its tail. It can float just slightly using its wings.

name: Larry's Dudunsparce ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Work Rush
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

name: Delcatty

attacks.name: Energy Crush
attacks.text: This attack does 40 damage for each Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: It dislikes dirty places. It often searches for a comfortable place in which to groom itself.

name: Zangoose ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Spike Draw
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Wild Scissors
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Larry's Starly

attacks.name: Minor Errand-Running
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: Because they are weak individually, they form groups. However, they bicker if the group grows too big.

name: Larry's Staravia
flavorText: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.

name: Larry's Staraptor

attacks.name: Facade
attacks.text: If this Pokémon is Burned or Poisoned, this attack does 100 more damage.

attacks.name: Feathery Strike
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon, and this attack also does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It never stops attacking even if it is injured. It fusses over the shape of its comb.

name: Mega Audino ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
Mega Evolution ex Rule: When your Mega Evolution Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Kaleidowaltz
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Ear Force
attacks.text: This attack does 80 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Larry's Rufflet

attacks.name: Peck the Wound
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 80 more damage.

flavorText: With its sharp claws, this Pokémon pierces its prey, and then it pecks at them. Although it also consumes berries, it’s a carnivore at heart.

name: Larry's Braviary

attacks.name: Clutch
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Brave Bird
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

flavorText: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of the sky will not stop battling, even if injured.

name: Larry's Komala

abilities.name: Lethargic Charge
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may use this Ability. Attach an Energy card from your hand to your Active Larry's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dozing Draw
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Asleep. Draw 2 cards.

flavorText: A potent anesthetic can be made by diluting Komala’s drool. This anesthetic was used for surgeries in the past.

name: Drampa

attacks.name: Dragon Strike
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Dragon Strike.

flavorText: It has a compassionate personality, but if it is angered, it completely destroys its surroundings with its intense breath.

name: Anthea & Concordia
rules: You can use this card only if you have N's Darmanitan, N's Zoroark ex, N's Vanilluxe, N's Klinklang, N's Reshiram, and N's Zekrom in play.  During this turn, if your opponent's Active Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack used by your N's Pokémon, take 3 more Prize cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Canari
rules: You can use this card only if you discard another card from your hand.  Search your deck for up to 4 Lightning Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Light Ball
rules: Attacks used by the Pikachu ex this card is attached to do 50 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon ex (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.

name: Nighttime Mine
rules: Attacks used by each Tera Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) cost Colorless more.
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it next to the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can’t be played.

name: Poké Pad
rules: Search your deck for a Pokémon that doesn't have a Rule Box, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. (Pokémon ex, Pokémon V, etc. have Rule Boxes.)
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Team Rocket's Hypnotizer
rules: If the Team Rocket's Pokémon this card is attached to is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon (even if this Team Rocket's Pokémon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Asleep.
You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.

name: Thick Scale
rules: The Dragon Pokémon this card is attached to takes 50 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Grass, Fire, Water, or Lightning Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.

name: Urbain
rules: Draw 3 cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Waitress
rules: Look at the top 6 cards of your deck and attach a Basic Energy card you find there to 1 of your Pokémon. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Sprigatito ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Magical Leaf
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.
